ABUJA – The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Caucus in the House of Representatives has felicitated with the governor of Sokoto State, RT. Hon. Aminu Waziri Tambuwal, on the occasion of his 56th birthday anniversary. In a goodwill message issued by the Caucus and signed by its leader, Hon. Kingsley Chinda (Rivers), the lawmakers described the chairman of the PDP Governors Forum as an “amiable leader” worthy of celebration. The statement reads: “The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) caucus, House of Representatives joins several well-meaning Nigerians to rejoice with and congratulate our amiable leader, His Excellency, Rt. Hon. Aminu Tambuwal, the Governor of Sokoto State and Chairman Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) Governors Forum.” “Clearly, today’s birthday anniversary marks 19 years of total commitment and dedicated service by His Excellency to God, humanity and the Nigerian State, and thus ought to be celebrated. “As a caucus, we are very pleased and delighted with your personality, kind disposition, sagacity, achievements and positive contributions to the political development of Nigeria and the general good of society at large,all of which have stood you out as not just a quintessential leader, but also a great statesman. “Whilst we heartily rejoice with you on this day, we hereby wish you many fruitful years of good health, greater achievements and untiring service to mankind and your fatherland. “Once again, congratulations,your Excellency and do accept our best wishes and prayers,” the statement added.